top.value: Centenary Action Group has called on the UK government to deliver real change for womens lives in the UK and around the world. Specifically: To implement Section 106 of the Equality Act 2010, requiring political parties to publish their candidate diversity data, and create positive pressure for change; To end harassment in the workplace through introducing a mandatory preventative duty on employers, reinstating third party harassment laws, and championing a progressive ILO Convention at the global level.

CARE India will carry out relief distribution (Shelter NFI*; WASH NFI and other Households items**) in Kumartchi block in Cuddalore district. This block is one among the six severely affected. Kumartchi also has more than 70% of Dalit population: this community has emerged as one of the most affected and vulnerable communities in the assessements conducted by the TN IAG, in which CARE also participated.
